T1  - A temporal cross-section approach to the price equation
AU  - Barth, James
AU  - Kraft, Arthur
AU  - Kraft, John
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 11
IS  - 2
SP  - 335
EP  - 351
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/10/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(79)90044-7
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407679900447
AB  - The purpose of this paper is to estimate a price equation for the manufacturing sector of the U.S. utilizing temporal cross-section industry data. Unlike previous studies which have not allowed for differences in behavior across industries, however, the parameters of our aggregate price equation are allowed to vary freely across manufacturing industries. To the extent that industries reflect differences in both product demands and costs of factor inputs, the estimation of a price equation permitting varying rather than fixed parameters seems preferable. The temporal cross-section specification will provide a microeconomic foundation to our aggregate price equation as well as permit us to take account of differences in individual industry parameters.
ER  - 

