AB  - In this note we propose a modification of the Cochrane-Orcutt iterative procedure for the computation of maximum likelihood estimates in a linear regression model with autocorrelated disturbances which possesses faster asymptotical convergence rate. The theoretical properties are shown to be supported by experimental results.
